lf._running = False\n    55\t    self.logger = logger.bind(channel=self.name)   
# ← drop this comment\n    56\t```\n    57\t\n    58\t✅ Clean, no comment, cons
istent:\n    59\t\n    60\t```python\n    61\tdef __init__(self, config: Any, bu
s: MessageBus):\n    62\t    self.config = config\n    63\t    self.bus = bus\n 
  64\t    self._running = False\n    65\t    self.logger = logger.bind(channel=s
elf.name)\n    66\t```\n    67\t\n    68\t✅ Rare case that genuinely needs a *w
hy*, in English:\n    69\t\n    70\t```python\n    71\t# Bind channel name into 
