402\tmetrics = ["observability-prometheus"]\n   403\t\n   404\t# WASM plugin exe
cution choice:\n   405\t#\n   406\t# Omit all three of the following features an
d there will not be any WASM plugin\n   407\t# support at all — no plugin runtim
e, no WASM dependencies, and the plugin ABI\n   408\t# surface will be unavailab
le in the agent runtime.\n   409\t#\n   410\t# Each feature adds a WASM executio
n strategy; enable the smallest set your targets\n   411\t# need. `plugins-wasm-
runtime-only` is implied by the other two. Every backend\n   412\t# feature also
implies `plugins-wasm` itself, so enabling any execution strategy\n   413\t# alw
ays carries the plugin host and its CLI surface; a backend-only build\n   414\t#
cannot silently produce a binary without the `plugin` subcommand.\n   415\t#\n  
416\t# - `plugins-wasm-runtime-only`: Fastest startup for plugins and smallest b
inary size,\n   417\t#   but requires plugin authors to compile a specific versi
on for each target\n   418\t#   architecture (`.cwasm` files instead of `.wasm`)
unless one of the two JIT\n   419\t#   compilation feature flags is also used.\n
  420\t# - `plugins-wasm-cranelift`: Add the Cranelift JIT compilation engine on
top of\n   421\t#   the runtime which enables compiling WASM plugins on the host
machine, but\n   422\t#   results in larger binary size due to the Cranelift dep
endency. NOTE: Not\n   423\t#   supported on all platforms (e.g., ARM32).\n   42
4\t# - `plugins-wasm-pulley`: Most flexible, supports JIT compilation on targets
\n   425\t#   where Cranelift isn\'t available (e.g., ARM32), but has the slowes
t runtime\n   426\t#   performance.\n   427\tplugins-wasm-runtime-only = ["plugi
ns-wasm", "zeroclaw-plugins/plugins-wasmtime"]\n   428\tplugins-wasm-cranelift  
 = ["plugins-wasm", "zeroclaw-plugins/plugins-wasm-cranelift"]\n   429\tplugins-
wasm-pulley       = ["plugins-wasm", "zeroclaw-plugins/plugins-wasm-pulley"]\n  
