fixed. #556\n\n**Important: This completely breaks pre v4.0 states.**\n\n**Impor
tant: The Pueue daemon needs to be restarted and the state will be wiped clean.*
*\n\n-  **Breaking**: Streamlined `pueue log` parameters to behave the same way 
as `start`, `pause` or `kill`. #509\n\n-  **Breaking**: Remove the `--children` 
commandline flags, that have been deprecated and no longer serve any function si
nce `v3.0.0`.\n\n-  Send log output to `stderr` instead of `stdout` #562.\n\n-  
Change default log level from error to warning #562.\n\n-  Bumped MSRV to 1.85 a
nd Rust edition to 2024.\n\n-  **Breaking**: Redesigned task editing process #55
3.\n\nPueue now allows editing all properties a task in one editor session. Ther
e\'re two modes to do so: `toml` and `files`, which is configurable via the `cli
ent.edit_mode` settings field.\n\n-  Revisited, fixed and cleaned up CLI help te
xts.\n\n-  Print most of Pueue\'s info/log messages to `stderr`. Only keep usefu
l stuff like json and task log output on `stdout`.\n\n-  **Breaking**: Allow `--
immediate` flag instead of `--start--immediately` on `pueue restart` for consist
ency with `pueue add`.\n\n-  **Breaking**: Ported from `anyhow` to `color_eyre` 
