sk: <prompt>`.\n2. BH sends a `think` request to Witt Brain.\n3. Witt Brain stre
ams `Chunk` events or returns a full `ThinkResponse`.\n4. BH renders `witt: <ans
wer>`.\n\n## A `think` request\nSame as `ask`, but Witt Brain is asked to includ
e a reasoning trace in the response. BH shows the trace first, then the answer.\
n\n## Tool use\n1. Witt Brain proposes a `ToolCall`.\n2. BH prints `do: <call>` 
and waits for explicit approval (or a configured auto-allow list).\n3. On approv
al, BH executes locally and returns a `ToolResult` event.\n4. Witt Brain continu
es.\n```\n\nguardrails.md:\n```markdown\n# Guardrails\n\n- **Refuse destructive 
